-- McLaren’s Hamilton Wins 3rd Pole of Season at Spanish Grand Prix
-- B y   B o b   B e n s c h
-- 2012-05-12T13:56:43Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-12/mclaren-s-hamilton-wins-3rd-pole-of-season-at-spanish-grand-prix.html
McLaren’s  Lewis Hamilton  topped
qualifying for tomorrow’s  Spanish Grand Prix  to earn his third
pole position of the season.  Hamilton beat out Williams’s Pastor Maldonado by 0.6
seconds in Barcelona to give McLaren its 150th Formula One pole.
Hamilton has qualified first or second for all five races this
season but has yet to win  Ferrari’s Fernando Alonso was third-fastest ahead of Lotus
teammates Romain Grosjean and Kimi Raikkonen. Sauber’s Sergio
Perez, Mercedes’s Nico Rosberg, two-time defending world
champion and current series leader Sebastian Vettel of Red Bull,
Mercedes’s Michael Schumacher and Sauber’s Kamui Kobayashi
rounded out the top-10 qualifiers.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Bob Bensch at 
 bbensch@bloomberg.net  